08:09.600 --> 08:13.400
do you feel comfortable asking the family
if they'd be willing to open THE SERVICE UP TO THE PUBLIC?

08:13.400 --> 08:16.600
- why's that? - we feel if they do, 
there's a good chance the unsub will come.

08:16.600 --> 08:17.800
i'll go speak to them.

08:18.600 --> 08:21.200
craig, we'd like you and your wife to consider
being there as well.

08:21.300 --> 08:22.400
good. anything.

08:22.400 --> 08:24.000
i think you should talk
to amy about it.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.400
if it might help,
there's nothing to discuss.

08:25.400 --> 08:28.800
i understand. but, please,
just...discuss it with her.

08:46.700 --> 08:48.400
when the police asked
for a picture of michael,

08:48.400 --> 08:50.500
i couldn't decide
what to give them.

08:51.400 --> 08:53.900
i didn't know if it was
right for him to be smiling.

08:54.100 --> 08:56.000
any choice you made
would have been right.

08:58.400 --> 09:00.600
my husband doesn't know
what to do with himself.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.200
he thinks we should be
out there looking for him.

09:04.300 --> 09:07.900
the best thing for you right now 
is to just let us guide you through this.

09:08.700 --> 09:10.200
he thinks i blame him.

09:10.700 --> 09:12.100
i'm sure that's not true.

09:12.100 --> 09:13.100
he's right.

09:15.100 --> 09:16.700
my son's been taken.

09:16.800 --> 09:17.700
i'm completely frozen.

09:17.700 --> 09:19.800
and now i'm blaming
my husband.

09:23.700 --> 09:25.200
i feel like a monster.

09:27.100 --> 09:30.100
when they need you,
you'll come through.

09:30.200 --> 09:31.700
you don't even know me.

09:32.000 --> 09:33.500
call it intuition.

09:46.500 --> 09:49.200
i found it when i came into his room,
after he'd been taken.

09:51.100 --> 09:52.800
we don't let him eat in bed.

09:54.300 --> 09:56.000
i haven't moved it
because...

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
i don't want him to think he's in trouble
for breaking the rules.

10:07.200 --> 10:08.700
you know what you're having?

10:10.200 --> 10:12.300
it's--it's a boy.

10:16.900 --> 10:18.700
congratulations.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.100
- garcia, you ready?
- ready.

10:25.500 --> 10:26.800
mr. bridges, let's go back
over what we discussed.

10:26.800 --> 10:28.200
- he's got my son.
- exactly.

10:28.200 --> 10:31.400
just stay positive.
i've written down some important phrases--

10:31.400 --> 10:32.500
we need to answer the phone.

10:32.500 --> 10:33.600
mr. bridges, please.

10:33.600 --> 10:35.700
i think amy should do this.

10:35.700 --> 10:37.000
she doesn't want to do this.

10:37.100 --> 10:38.200
no. i don't.

10:38.200 --> 10:41.400
it's our experience that the parent that's
least emotional is best.

10:43.400 --> 10:44.900
amy, you'll be great.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.100
just try to humanize michael
at every opportunity.

10:47.100 --> 10:48.800
he needs to see him
as a person.

10:48.800 --> 10:51.600
try to keep him on the line as long
as you possibly can.

10:51.600 --> 10:54.200
the more he talks,
the more he'll reveal about himself.

10:56.600 --> 10:57.500
hello.

10:57.500 --> 10:58.700
are you alone?

11:00.100 --> 11:02.100
um, my husband is with me.

11:02.100 --> 11:05.400
why are you just sitting at home
when you should be out looking for your boy?

11:07.700 --> 11:10.600
you're right.
we need to do that.

11:11.100 --> 11:12.800
he's better off with me.

11:13.700 --> 11:16.600
thank you for calling us
to let us know michael's all right.

11:17.000 --> 11:18.500
i didn't say
he was all right.

11:19.500 --> 11:23.900
i know. i'm--i'm just
trusting that he's ok.

11:24.100 --> 11:25.800
he's in a better place now.

11:29.200 --> 11:30.400
may i speak with michael?

11:30.400 --> 11:31.900
he doesn't want
to talk to you.

11:32.300 --> 11:34.000
he knows what a bad mother
you are.

11:34.400 --> 11:35.600
your 3 minutes are up.

11:43.100 --> 11:44.300
garcia, anything?

11:44.400 --> 11:45.900
it looks to be
a disposable cell phone.

11:45.900 --> 11:49.600
i couldn't triangulate the call. 
but it did bounce off not one but 2 towers.

11:49.600 --> 11:50.900
- meaning?
- i know he's mobile.

11:50.900 --> 11:52.600
and i know he's moving
within the las vegas limits.

11:52.600 --> 11:54.200
he didn't travel
outside the city.

11:55.400 --> 11:56.400
it's just a start.

11:56.900 --> 11:59.400
like i said, the more he talks,
the more we'll learn about him.

11:59.700 --> 12:01.600
these are agents
morgan and reid.

12:01.600 --> 12:03.900
they'll be here all night
just in case he calls back.

12:04.500 --> 12:05.800
i need to lie down.

12:06.100 --> 12:07.100
of course.

12:09.700 --> 12:11.000
you should go with her.

12:11.400 --> 12:12.400
yeah.

12:15.400 --> 12:17.300
what'd you find out
from the medical examiner?

12:17.500 --> 12:19.200
we think that
he's starving them.

12:19.300 --> 12:21.800
but that doesn't fit with the care he takes
with the bodies.

12:21.800 --> 12:23.600
starvation would be
a form of torture.

12:23.600 --> 12:24.900
there's no sexual assault.

12:25.100 --> 12:27.300
the torture could be
a substitute for the sex act.

12:28.300 --> 12:29.700
i'll coordinate
with rossi and prentiss.

12:29.700 --> 12:31.200
we'll call you
if there's anything new.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.900
couldn't find any evidence
of forced entry.

13:18.900 --> 13:20.200
why would that matter?

13:22.000 --> 13:24.300
'cause it means he most likely knew
his attacker.

13:25.500 --> 13:26.500
reid?

13:28.700 --> 13:30.500
get 'em off. morgan!
get 'em off! get 'em off!

13:30.500 --> 13:31.700
morgan, get 'em off me!
get 'em off me!

13:31.700 --> 13:33.800
get 'em off me!

13:33.800 --> 13:35.400
get 'em--
morgan, get 'em off me!

13:35.400 --> 13:37.100
reid. reid. wake up.

13:37.100 --> 13:37.900
it's morgan.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.100
what the hell's going on?

13:40.200 --> 13:41.800
sir, ma'am.
everything's ok.

13:41.800 --> 13:44.000
you wake us up screaming,
you think everything's ok?

13:44.000 --> 13:46.100
i understand we startled you.
and i'm sorry for that.

13:46.100 --> 13:47.400
you're the f.b.i.

13:47.800 --> 13:50.600
you're right.
i'm really sorry.

13:52.000 --> 13:56.200
sir, please, go back upstairs 
and try to get some rest.

13:56.200 --> 13:57.500
it was just
a misunderstanding.

13:57.500 --> 13:59.700
everything is fine,
i promise you that.

14:07.600 --> 14:08.900
are you ok?

14:09.600 --> 14:11.600
it was a dream.
i'm really sorry.

14:12.200 --> 14:13.400
was it about michael?

14:15.600 --> 14:16.900
no.

14:17.700 --> 14:19.600
i've been afraid
to close my eyes.

14:23.100 --> 14:25.000
i'm scared i'll see him die.

14:27.500 --> 14:29.800
ma'am, i know it's hard.

14:30.900 --> 14:33.500
but i need you to go upstairs 
and try to get some sleep.

14:34.800 --> 14:35.900
please.

14:37.100 --> 14:39.000
i am sorry
for the disturbance.

14:47.900 --> 14:49.400
i'm making everything worse.

14:50.200 --> 14:51.000
reid...

14:54.300 --> 14:56.100
these cases get to all of us.

14:56.200 --> 14:57.500
i'm losing it
in their living room.

14:57.500 --> 14:58.800
and i'm dreaming--

15:00.000 --> 15:04.900
i'm dreaming about dead kids
and covered in leeches.

15:05.200 --> 15:06.700
what the hell is scaring you?

15:09.600 --> 15:12.400
this boy's gonna die
and there's nothing i can do to stop it.

15:38.100 --> 15:40.600
i can't do this.
i'm sorry.

15:42.100 --> 15:43.000
what are you doing?

15:43.200 --> 15:44.300
i'm not going to the funeral.

15:44.300 --> 15:45.300
we talked about this.

15:45.300 --> 15:47.200
no, you talked. i listened.

15:47.200 --> 15:49.700
please, tell her
this is our only chance.

